main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a green object with a white rim moving from east to west in Security, Colorado on March 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 4-5 seconds at tree top level before disappearing behind trees., The object was described as being as bright as a car headlight., The report concludes the sighting was due to a meteor., The observer reported this sighting to local police the day after the event., No photographs or physical evidence were documented in the report.
sighted object: one green object with a white rim
